{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, the representations from these two networks are combined using a fully connected layer, and the final label is determined.",
    "Uncertainty poses another challenge in disinformation detection.",
    "Uncertainty in the propagation graph of disinformation is inevitable.",
    "On one hand, disinformation producers often manipulate others by generating fake supporting tweets or eliminating opposing voices in order to evade detection.",
    "On the other hand, the available graph may only represent a portion of the actual propagation structure and may include noisy relations, leading to inherent uncertainty Wei et al. (2021)."
  ]
}